<h5 data-zesty-id="content:text:1:8">The Women's Auxiliary Mission Statement</h5>
<p data-zesty-id="content:textarea:2:58">
	The Women’s Auxiliary functions as a fundraising and volunteer service group that seeks to support The Salvation Army in its mission of spiritual redemption and social rehabilitation of those it serves.
</p>
<div class="my-4" data-zesty-id="design:design:whitespace-md:3:82"></div>
<h5 data-zesty-id="content:text:4:72">Statement of Purpose</h5>
<p data-zesty-id="content:textarea:5:60">
	To promote and support the work of The Salvation Army and to strengthen the hands of those who have dedicated their lives to its cause.
</p>
<div class="my-4" data-zesty-id="design:design:whitespace-md:6:27"></div>
<h5 data-zesty-id="content:text:7:66">Join Us</h5>
<p data-zesty-id="content:textarea:8:64">
	The Salvation Army Women’s Auxiliary of Greenville is the only auxiliary in the state of South Carolina. &nbsp;It is a committed volunteer group dedicated to doing the most good in our community. Meetings are held on the 2nd Wednesday of each month (except July) at 11:30 a.m. at the Kroc Center located at 42 Westfield Street in Greenville (lunch is served).&nbsp;
</p>
<p data-zesty-id="content:wysiwyg_basic:9:31">
	For more information about SAWA memberships, please email the Women's Auxiliary Coordinator:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:amanda.link@uss.salvationarmy.org" target="">Amanda Link</a>
</p>
<div class="my-2" data-zesty-id="design:design:whitespace-sm:10:78"></div>
<p data-zesty-id="content:textarea:11:55">
	If you are interested in joining SAWA, please visit the link below.&nbsp;
</p>
<p style="text-align:center;" class="cta-button-group d-flex flex-wrap gap-2 my-3 justify-content-center" data-zesty-id="content:wysiwyg_basic:12:19"><a href="https://migration.salvationarmy.org/greenvillesc/become-a-sawa-member?random=662" class="btn btn-secondary gap-1 mt-2">Become a Member Today</a></p>
<div class="my-2" data-zesty-id="design:design:whitespace-sm:13:71"></div>
